  "educationalNotes": "Berkelium is named after Berkeley, California - element after californium! Berkelium-247 half-life 1,380 years. Alpha emitter produced in nuclear reactors. Berkelium-249 produces californium via neutron absorption. Discovered in 1949. Minute quantities produced - research only. Radiotoxic - biological actinide (accumulates in bone). Medical research interest. Extremely expensive - <1 gram produced annually."
